German Hearing Aid Maker Kind to Expand, Handelsblatt Says

-- B y   R i c h a r d   W e i s s
-- 
2011-08-26T06:12:54Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-26/german-hearing-aid-maker-kind-to-expand-handelsblatt-says.html
Kind  Hoergeraete GmbH & Co. KG, the
German hearing-aid maker, plans to increase the number of stores
nationwide to 800 in coming years from 500 and add stores
abroad,  Handelsblatt  reported, citing Alexander Kind, the
company’s head.  Hoergeraete isn’t worried by  Fielmann AG (FIE) ’s plans to expand
into hearing aids, Kind also told the newspaper.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Richard Weiss  in  Frankfurt  at 
 rweiss5@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Benedikt Kammel at   bkammel@bloomberg.net . 